Phising Website Detection Using Machine Learning Techniques

In today's interconnected world, cyber attacks have become a disturbingly common occurrence, posing a significant and persistent threat to individuals, organizations, and even nations.phising being a common cyber attack where people impersonate trusted organisation with malicious intentions this project detects phising websites to curb this problem

Distribution Of Data with respect to the 'label' Column (phishing vs legitimate).

The Label Encoding has 0 Rep Legit Domains and 1 Rep Phising Websites

In[]:
binary_feature = ['Have_IP']

for feature in binary_feature:
    label_counts = df.groupby(feature)['Label'].value_counts()
    label_proportions = df.groupby(feature)['Label'].value_counts()

    # Example using Seaborn for a more direct grouped bar
    sns.countplot(data=df, x=feature, hue='Label')
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {feature} by Website Type(Legitimate and phising website)')
    plt.xlabel(feature)
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(title='Website Type')
    plt.show()
